The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on January 15, 2021, declaring January 18, 2021, as the Martin Luther King, Jr., Federal Holiday. The proclamation honors and celebrates Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr., a prominent figure in the civil rights movement. It highlights Dr. King's call for equality, justice, and nonviolent resistance to injustices such as racial segregation and employment discrimination. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of meeting anger with compassion and working towards healing past injustices. It also mentions the administration's efforts to create jobs, uplift communities, support Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCUs), and promote educational and economic empowerment for minority communities. The proclamation encourages all Americans to engage in acts of service to honor Dr. King's dream and uphold his legacy.